data.title: United Therapeutics beat Q4 earnings estimate with $7.70 earnings per share. Sales were $790.200 million, missing estimate. CEO is optimistic about future clinical programs.
data.description: United Therapeutics Corp (NASDAQ: UTHR) exceeded expectations in their fourth-quarter earnings report, revealing earnings of $7.70 per share, surpassing the estimated $7.09 per share. However, the company fell short of the projected $813.077 million in quarterly sales with reported sales totaling $790.200 million. Martine Rothblatt, Ph.D., Chairperson and Chief Executive Officer of United Therapeutics, expressed gratitude towards the team for achieving record total revenue for the fourth consecutive year. The company is eagerly anticipating the results of their ADVANCE OUTCOMES and TETON-1 clinical programs which have the potential to introduce new treatment alternatives for patients.

data.title: Business travel surpasses leisure as main factor driving private aviation in 2026, marking stable growth post-pandemic.
data.description: ALTOUR, a company under Internova Travel Group, announced in New York on Feb. 26, 2026, that private aviation is transitioning into a steadier and more mature phase this year. Following the pandemic-induced fluctuations, the industry is now experiencing stabilization, with demand leveling off. Business travel, which had seen significant disruptions, is gradually returning to normal. This marks a shift from the previous years of rapid growth and unpredictability.

data.title: Medline Inc (MDLN) reported Q4 loss of 1 cent/share, missed earnings estimate, but beat sales estimate at $7.787B. CEO pleased with $2.4B new customer signings in 2025.
data.description: Medline Inc (NASDAQ: MDLN) released its fourth-quarter results recently, presenting a mixed report. The company recorded a loss of 1 cent per share, falling short of the expected earnings of 18 cents per share according to analysts. However, in terms of quarterly sales, Medline exceeded expectations by reporting $7.787 billion, surpassing the projected $7.547 billion. Jim Boyle, the CEO of Medline, expressed satisfaction with the results, highlighting the closure of a successful 2025 with $2.4 billion in new customer signings. This achievement signifies the trust customers have in the company's value proposition.

data.title: Eaton raises dividend to $1.10/share, up 6%. Dividend payable March 27, 2026, to shareholders as of March 10, 2026.
data.description: In Dublin, the Board of Directors of Eaton, a leading intelligent power management company listed as NYSE:ETN, announced a 6% increase in their quarterly dividend to $1.10 per ordinary share. data.title: Ethan Allen's Mexico plant in Silao, Guanajuato, honored for 7th year for socially and environmentally responsible practices.
data.description: In Danbury, Connecticut on February 26, 2026, Ethan Allen's upholstery manufacturing facility in Silao, Guanajuato, Mexico has received the "Empresa Socialmente Responsable" (Environmentally and Socially Responsible Company) designation for the seventh year in a row. This prestigious recognition is awarded by the Mexican Center for Corporate Philanthropy and the Alliance for Corporate Social Responsibility, highlighting the plant's ongoing commitment to environmental and social responsibility.

data.title: IonQ (NYSE: IONQ) reported Q4 revenue of $61.9 million, up 429% YoY, surpassing expectations. Stock up 20% in response. Company hit $130 million for full year, signaling strong commercial growth in quantum computing sector. Investors optimistic about future.
data.description: IonQ Inc. (NYSE: IONQ) has reported impressive fourth-quarter results, marking a significant shift in the quantum computing sector from theoretical promise to tangible commercial growth. The company's stock is on the rise, reflecting investor confidence. In Q4, IonQ recorded a substantial revenue beat of $61.9 million, showcasing a remarkable 429% increase from the previous year and surpassing Wall Street's projections. This robust performance extended to the full year, with IonQ achieving $130 million in revenue, becoming the first pure-play quantum company to surpass the $100 million annual revenue milestone. As a result, shares surged by nearly 20% in a single trading session. IonQ's success not only benefitted the company but also boosted the entire quantum sector, demonstrating the increasing willingness of customers to invest in quantum services. This development signifies a promising start for quantum businesses as they move into a phase of commercial viability.

data.title: Teladoc Health beats Q4 earnings, posts sales of $642.269M vs $635.235M estimates; FY2026 loss forecast cut to $(1.10)-$(0.70) vs $(0.76) estimates; expects sales of $2.47B-$2.587B vs $2.548B estimates.
data.description: Teladoc Health Inc (NYSE: TDOC) reported a strong performance for Q4 with a quarterly loss of 14 cents per share, surpassing market expectations of an 18 cents per share loss. The company's sales reached $642.269 million, exceeding estimates of $635.235 million. For FY2026, Teladoc Health anticipates a GAAP loss ranging between $(1.10)-$(0.70) compared to market projections of $(0.76). Revenue outlook for the year is between $2.470 billion-$2.587 billion, while estimates stood at $2.548 billion. The company's CEO expressed optimism about the results, highlighting achievements in various strategic areas.

data.title: EventWorks 4D collaborates on Europe's first interactive AI Holocaust testimony theater, expanding immersive capabilities.
data.description: In Essen, Germany, on February 26, 2026, EventWorks 4D revealed their partnership in introducing Europe's pioneering interactive AI Holocaust testimony theater, known as the Holo-Voices Theater. The Holo-Voices Theater promises to provide a unique experience, blending historical narratives with cutting-edge technology for educational purposes.
